President Biden has declared a major disaster in Alabama due to severe storms, straight-line winds, and tornadoes that occurred from March 24 to March 27, 2023. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. The affected counties include Chambers, Colbert, Coosa, Elmore, Lauderdale, Macon, Marion, Morgan, Randolph, and Tallapoosa. Federal funding is available for emergency work, facility repairs or replacements, and hazard mitigation measures. Kevin A. Wallace, Sr. of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations, and additional designations may be made in the future if requested by the state and based on damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA news desk.